  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Houston, Texas Flood Response</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="4">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">All Hands Volunteers will be mucking, gutting and sanitizing homes that have been damaged by the catastrophic flooding in Houston. Communities that are most in need will be receiving assistance from our group of volunteers on the ground. Through partnerships with local organizations on the ground we will work to assist the people of Houston and give them the resources to start to recover from this tragedy.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Houston is experiencing a catastrophic situation after 17 inches of rain fell in less than 24 hours in communities across the city. More than 1,000 homes have been damaged, as well as other community spaces, businesses and schools. Rivers and streams continue to rise which adds to the growing need for assistance. As a result of the increasingly perilous situation our long time partner, UMCOR-TX, has asked All Hands Volunteers to come to Texas and bring our disaster assessment tools and volunteer coordination expertise.</narrative>
  </description>
